@jomuel Right, but the other classes are standard python classes, and even for `Greenlet`, I suppose a inherited class with same name as a import-time drop-in replacement would require less refactoring, something in the lines:
```
from gevent import Greenlet as GGreenlet

class Greenlet(GGreenlet):
    is_safe_linked = True
    def link(self, callable):
        return super().link(_wrap_link_callable(callable)
    ...
```
then just `from raiden.utils.gevent_utils import Greenlet` instead of importing from `gevent`, and no other changes to the calls should be required, no?
